title=Greece's Competitive Advantage|last=Mourdoukoutas|first=Panos|work=Forbes|access-date=2018-07-25|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nMIKEL launched its first coffee store in 2008 in the city of [[Larissa]].<ref name=\"mikelcc2\"/> In the years that followed, MIKEL gradually expanded throughout [[Greece]] with the city of [[Volos]] being the starting point.<ref name=\"mikelcc2\"/> As of recently, MIKEL has expanded beyond Greece, launching its first coffee store in the [[United Arab Emirates]] in 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://coffeebi.com/2017/06/26/mikel-coffee-company-expanding-in-uae/|title=CoffeeBI - Mikel Coffee Company to Expand in UAE|date=2017-06-26|work=CoffeeBI|access-date=2018-01-16|language=en-US}}</ref> The company has already opened seven stores in Dubai and imposed itself as an important competitor in its sector.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenationalherald.com/160230/forbes-greek-start-up-mikel-cause-competition-problems-to-starbucks-in-dubai/|title=Forbes: Greek Start-up Mikel Cause Competition Problems to Starbucks in Dubai|date=2017-05-02|work=The National Herald|access-date=2018-01-16|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/panosmourdoukoutas/2017/04/30/starbucks-little-greek-problem-in-dubai-mikel/#119951916bff|title=Starbucks' Little Greek Problem In Dubai -- Mikel|last=Mourdoukoutas|first=Panos|work=Forbes|access-date=2018-01-16|language=en}}</ref> As of March 2018, the company has also begun operating in London.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.news247.gr/epixeiriseis/mikel-premiera-sto-londino-kai-stis-pente-hpeiroys-mesa-stis-epomenes-60-hmeres.6591334.html|title=Mikel: Premiere in London - All five continents within the next 60 days|language=el}}</ref> As of August 2018, the company has also opened their first store in Australia. As of September 2018, the company has also opened their first store in U.S.A.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/panosmourdoukoutas/2018/09/08/starbucks-greek-problem-in-australia-mikel-coffee-community/#7085a94f3647|title=Starbucks' Greek Problem In Australia: Mikel Coffee Community|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Brand ==\nThe brand name, stylized as \"MIKEL,\" stands for \"Maybe it's knowledge entering life\", the company's [[motto]].<ref name=\"mikelcc2\"/> The brand logo features the father of its founder, Eleftherios Kyriakakis.<ref name=\"mikelcc2\"/>\n\n==Locations== \nAs of March 2020 there were 242 stores in the following countries:\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Country\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Number of stores\n|-\n| [[Greece]]\n| 206\n|-\n| [[Cyprus]]\n| 20\n|-\n| [[United Arab Emirates]]\n| 4\n|-\n| [[Bulgaria]]\n| 2\n|-\n| [[United Kingdom]]\n| 2\n|-\n| [[United States]]\n| 2\n|-\n| [[Australia]]\n| 2\n|-\n|[[Saudi Arabia]]\n| 2\n|-\n|[[Romania]]\n| 1\n|-\n| [[Egypt]]\n| 1\n|-\n| [[Germany]]\n| Upcoming\n|-\n| [[Canada]]\n| Upcoming\n\n[[Category:Companies established in 2008]]\n[[Category:Coffeehouses of Greece]]\n[[Category:Coffee companies]]\n[[Category:Greek brands]]\n[[Category:Companies based in Larissa]]\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n", "name_user": "Stella Marini", "label": "safe", "comment": "update website", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mikel_Coffee_Company"}
{"title_page": "Helge Rode", "text_new": "[[File:Helge_Rode_and_Holger_Drachmann_in_Skagen.jpg|thumb|right|Authors [[Holger Drachmann]] (middle) and Ebbe Rode in [[Skagen]]]]\n\n'''Helge Rode''' ([[Frederiksberg]], 16 October 1870, 23 March 1937)<ref>[http://adl.dk/adl_pub/forfatter/e_forfatter/e_forfatter.xsql?ff_id=86&nnoc=adl_pub Helge Rode] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121227185452/http://adl.dk/adl_pub/forfatter/e_forfatter/e_forfatter.xsql?ff_id=86&nnoc=adl_pub |date=2012-12-27 }} at Arkiv for Dansk Litteratur</ref> was a [[Denmark|Danish]] writer and critic, and journalist for ''[[Politiken]]'', ''[[Berlingske Tidende]]'', and ''[[Illustreret Tidende]]''.<ref>[http://www.nomos-dk.dk/skraep/helge_rode-bio.htm Helge Rode (1870-1937)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081028135721/http://www.nomos-dk.dk/skraep/helge_rode-bio.htm |date=2008-10-28 }} at Nomos-DK.dk</ref> He was a son of [[Margrethe Vullum|Margrethe Rode]],<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Margrethe Vullum |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Irene |last=Iversen |authorlink= |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo |url=http://nbl.snl.no/Margrethe_Vullum/utdypning |language=Norwegian |accessdate=22 June 2013}}</ref> the brother of politician [[Ove Rode]],<ref name=\"encyklop\u00e6di\"/> and father of actor [[Ebbe Rode]].<ref>[http://www.gravsted.dk/person.php?navn=helgerode Helge Rode - Dansk forfatter] at Gravsted.dk</ref>\n\nHe was a critic of [[Georg Brandes]] and the [[Modern Breakthrough]].<ref name=\"encyklop\u00e6di\">[http://www.denstoredanske.dk/Kunst_og_kultur/Litteratur/Dansk_litteratur/1870-1900/Helge_Rode Helge Rode entry] at Gyldendal Encyklop\u00e6di</ref>. Composer [[Carl Nielsen]]'s piece [[Moderen]] (''The Mother'') was written for a play by Rode in 1920-21\n\n\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* {{Internet Archive author |sname=Helge Rode}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFA