{"title_page": "H\u00f8je Taastrup station", "text_new": "{{Infobox station \n| name          = H\u00f8je Taastrup\n| symbol        = S\n| symbol_location = Copenhagen\n| type          = [[List of S-train stations|S-train]] and [[:Category:Railway stations in Denmark|DSB]] station\n| style         = STL\n| image         = HT train station.JPG\n| image_caption = \n| address       = 5 Banestr\u00f8get, [[Taastrup]]\n| coordinates   = {{Coord|55|38|55|N|12|16|09|E|type:railwaystation_region:DK|display=inline,title}}\n| line          = <!-- line information is detailed under \"services\" -->\n| other         = \n| structure     = \n| platform      = 3 [[Island platforms]]\n| depth         = \n| levels        = \n| tracks        = 6\n| parking       = \n| bicycle       = \n| baggage_check = \n| opened        = 31 May 1986\n| closed        = \n| rebuilt       = \n| electrified   = 1986 (S-train), 1988 (Mainline)\n| ADA           = \n| code          = \n| owned         = [[DSB (railway company)|DSB]]\n| zone          = \n| smartcardname = \n| smartcardstatus = \n| former        = \n| passengers    = \n| pass_year     = \n| pass_percent  = \n| pass_system   = \n| mpassengers   = \n| services      = {{S-rail|title=STL}}\n{{S-line|system=STL|line=Bx|next=Taastrup|rows1=2}}\n{{S-line|system=STL|line=B|next=Taastrup|hide1=yes}}\n{{S-rail|title=DSB}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=ICCphStr|previous=K\u00f8benhavn H|next=Roskilde|rows1=2}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=ICCphTi|previous=K\u00f8benhavn H|next=Roskilde|hide1=yes}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=ICCphAb|previous=Valby|next=Roskilde|rows1=3}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=ICCphEs|previous=Valby|next=Roskilde|hide1=yes}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=ICCphPa|previous=Valby|next=Roskilde|hide1=yes|type2=Both}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=R40a|previous=Valby|next=Hedehusene|rows2=2}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=CphRos|previous=Valby|next=Hedehusene|type=Both|rows1=2|hide2=yes}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=R50|previous=Valby|next=Hedehusene|type=Both|hide1=yes}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=R54|previous=Valby|next=Roskilde|rows1=2|type2=Both}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=R56|previous=Valby|next=Hedehusene|hide1=yes}}\n{{s-rail|title=Deutsche Bahn}}\n{{s-line|system=DB-ICE|line=75|previous=Copenhagen Central|next=N\u00e6stved |type=}}\n| map_locator   = \n| web           = \n}}\n'''H\u00f8je Taastrup station''' ({{IPA-da|\u02c8h\u028cj\u0259 \u02c8ts\u02b0\u028c\u02ccst\u0281\u0254p st\u00e6\u02c8\u0255o\u02c0n}}) is a [[railway station]] in [[H\u00f8je-Taastrup]] municipality, [[Denmark]], opened on 31 May 1986.\n\nThe station is one of the largest in Denmark. It is the terminus of [[S-train]] services [[B (S-train)|B]] and [[Bx (S-train)|Bx]] on the [[Vestbanen (S-tog)|Taastrup radial]]. The station is further served by [[regional]], [[InterCity]] and even international [[train]]s.\n\nAt the south end of the railroad station complex stands \"Thor's Tower\" ''(Torst\u00e5rnet),'' the tallest sculpture in the Nordic countries. The railway station itself has three distinctive arches, which have become a symbol of the municipality, and have given rise to the moniker \"The City of Arches\" (Danish: ''Buernes By,'' which in a play on words sounds remarkably similar to the phrase ''Byernes By'' or \"The City of Cities\").\n\n[[File:H\u00f8je Taastrup Station in 1994.jpg|thumb|left|300px|H\u00f8je Taastrup Station in 1994]]\n{{clear left}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commonscat-inline|H\u00f8je Taastrup Station}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hoje Taastrup}}\n[[Category:Copenhagen S-train stations]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Copenhagen]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1986]]\n\n\n{{Denmark-railstation-stub}}\n{{Europe-metro-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox station \n| name          = H\u00f8je Taastrup\n| symbol        = S\n| symbol_location = Copenhagen\n| type          = [[List of S-train stations|S-train]] and [[:Category:Railway stations in Denmark|DSB]] station\n| style         = STL\n| image         = HT train station.JPG\n| image_caption = \n| address       = 5 Banestr\u00f8get, [[Taastrup]]\n| coordinates   = {{Coord|55|38|55|N|12|16|09|E|type:railwaystation_region:DK|display=inline,title}}\n| line          = <!-- line information is detailed under \"services\" -->\n| other         = \n| structure     = \n| platform      = 3 [[Island platforms]]\n| depth         = \n| levels        = \n| tracks        = 6\n| parking       = \n| bicycle       = \n| baggage_check = \n| opened        = 31 May 1986\n| closed        = \n| rebuilt       = \n| electrified   = 1986 (S-train), 1988 (Mainline)\n| ADA           = \n| code          = \n| owned         = [[DSB (railway company)|DSB]]\n| zone          = \n| smartcardname = \n| smartcardstatus = \n| former        = \n| passengers    = \n| pass_year     = \n| pass_percent  = \n| pass_system   = \n| mpassengers   = \n| services      = {{S-rail|title=STL}}\n{{S-line|system=STL|line=Bx|next=Taastrup|rows1=2}}\n{{S-line|system=STL|line=B|next=Taastrup|hide1=yes}}\n{{S-rail|title=DSB}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=ICCphStr|previous=K\u00f8benhavn H|next=Roskilde|rows1=2}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=ICCphTi|previous=K\u00f8benhavn H|next=Roskilde|hide1=yes}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=ICCphAb|previous=Valby|next=Roskilde|rows1=3}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=ICCphEs|previous=Valby|next=Roskilde|hide1=yes}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=ICCphPa|previous=Valby|next=Roskilde|hide1=yes|type2=Both}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=R40a|previous=Valby|next=Hedehusene|rows2=2}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=CphRos|previous=Valby|next=Hedehusene|type=Both|rows1=2|hide2=yes}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=R50|previous=Valby|next=Hedehusene|type=Both|hide1=yes}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=R54|previous=Valby|next=Roskilde|rows1=2|type2=Both}}\n{{S-line|system=DSB|line=R56|previous=Valby|next=Hedehusene|hide1=yes}}\n{{s-rail|title=Deutsche Bahn}}\n{{s-line|system=DB-ICE|line=75|previous=Copenhagen Central|next=N\u00e6stved |type=}}\n| map_locator   = \n| web           = \n}}\n'''H\u00f8je Taastrup station''' ({{IPA-da|\u02c8h\u028cj\u026a \u02c8ts\u02b0\u028c\u02ccst\u0281\u0254p st\u00e6\u02c8\u0255o\u02c0n}}) is a [[railway station]] in [[H\u00f8je-Taastrup]] municipality, [[Denmark]], opened on 31 May 1986.\n\nThe station is one of the largest in Denmark. It is the terminus of [[S-train]] services [[B (S-train)|B]] and [[Bx (S-train)|Bx]] on the [[Vestbanen (S-tog)|Taastrup radial]]. The station is further served by [[regional]], [[InterCity]] and even international [[train]]s.\n\nAt the south end of the railroad station complex stands \"Thor's Tower\" ''(Torst\u00e5rnet),'' the tallest sculpture in the Nordic countries. The railway station itself has three distinctive arches, which have become a symbol of the municipality, and have given rise to the moniker \"The City of Arches\" (Danish: ''Buernes By,'' which in a play on words sounds remarkably similar to the phrase ''Byernes By'' or \"The City of Cities\").\n\n[[File:H\u00f8je Taastrup Station in 1994.jpg|thumb|left|300px|H\u00f8je Taastrup Station in 1994]]\n{{clear left}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commonscat-inline|H\u00f8je Taastrup Station}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hoje Taastrup}}\n[[Category:Copenhagen S-train stations]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in Copenhagen]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1986]]\n\n\n{{Denmark-railstation-stub}}\n{{Europe-metro-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Nardog", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:fixingDanish IPA", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/H%C3%B8je_Taastrup_station"}
